message: Focus heavily on combination rules, as tools often create 'botched' features which severely reduce value. My only successful, positive value combination was two liquids ('kraken ink' + 'tree sap' -> 40 value). Other combinations, especially those mixing states (solid + gas/liquid) or even homogenous solids, consistently led to negative values. The 'vial' often results in 'failed extraction', and the 'filter' frequently adds 'botched filtering', both of which are detrimental. Use tools sparingly and cautiously, perhaps only on base ingredients or specific combinations you suspect might benefit from a single feature change, as they often worsen items with multiple features.

message: Avoid combining magical and mundane items directly; this often leads to negative values. The 'vial' tool is your best bet, but use it strategically. The most reliable path to positive value was this sequence: 1. Use 'vial' on a single magical liquid ingredient (e.g., basilisk venom, kraken ink). This will usually result in a low negative value item with 'botched extraction'. 2. Combine this 'botched extraction' magical liquid with a pure magical solid ingredient (e.g., sunstone). This will create a highly negative combined item. 3. Crucially, apply the 'vial' tool *again* to this newly combined, highly negative item. This action consistently produced positive-value items. The 'filter' tool generally degrades items or adds more negative features, so use it sparingly or not at all on items with 'botched' features, as it rarely improved them. Focus on the vial-combine-vial pattern with magical ingredients.

message: Focus on using the 'vial' tool on *single solid ingredients* first. This is the most consistent way to create positive-value extracts (e.g., mushroom, frog leg, unicorn horn, mandrake root all yield 30). Once you have two positive 'liquid, extracted' items, combining them can often increase their value (e.g., two 30-value extracts can become 60). Be cautious with the 'filter' tool and using the 'vial' on liquids or gases, as these actions usually lead to negative values or reductions.

message: To maximize your score, always prioritize using the 'vial' tool. Combining two solid, mundane ingredients first will yield a -100 value item (e.g., dandelion + obsidian). Applying the 'vial' to this item consistently transforms it into a 60-value item. Combining a solid and a liquid (even if one is magical) will often yield -60, which the 'vial' can improve to 50. The 'filter' tool consistently decreases value, so avoid using it on high-value items. Liquid-liquid combinations can sometimes yield positive values directly (e.g., kraken ink + tree sap = 40). Gas combinations generally fare poorly with the vial.
